  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal) [Modifiers: Repeater], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

records.addlTxt:
10:54 AM Defendant Eric W. Moses appeared by phone, in custody Monroe County Jail.  Attorney Carly June Sebion appeared by video for Eric W. Moses.  Attorney Jeri Marsolek in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant agrees to continue remotely.  Defendant pleads No contest to count 1 and count 2..

Court reviewed the elements and potential penalties of the charge the defendant plead to.  He understood.   Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant.  He understood. Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor (1) contrary to 946.49(1)(a), Habitual Criminality contrary to 939.62(1)(a); Operating While Revoked (1) contrary to 343.44(1)(b), Habitual Criminality (1) contrary to 939.62(1)(a). Defendant did not exercise his right to allocution.

State moves to amend the counts as listed in the amended criminal complaint. Court grants motion to amend counts contained in amended complaint.

Joint recommendation of costs only on both counts requests payment plan of $25/month starting 3/1/23. $886.00

Court adopts joint recommendation and orders costs on both counts totaling $886.00. Payment plan approved at $25/month beginning 3/1/23. Failure to pay ?  DNA
